{"name": "classdiff", "metadata": {"name": "classdiff", "version": "0.5.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["deepdiff"], "summary": "Utility to diff classes", "upload_time": 1719583786}, "documentation": ["# `classdiff` - Python Class Difffer\n\nThis is a small library to diff (data) classes or any other objects. It is\nintended two work one obejcts of the same time or `NoneType`. Diffing different\nclasses is possible but might result in unexpected result. Different from most\nexisting diff tools that produce data structures that show adds, removes or\nchanges, this tool is intended to use for printing a dataclass and higlight the\ndiff with different color coding, similar to the output of `Terraform` or\n`Pulumi`.\n\n## Usage\n\nJust pass your classes to the diff function to get back a representation of the\ndiff.\n\nGiven the following two classes:\n\n```python\nnew = SomeResource(\n    name=\"my-data\",\n    price=2.3,\n    quantity=4,\n    dangerous=True,\n    other=OtherClass(name=\"OA\"),\n    not_changed=OtherClass(name=\"Same\"),\n)\n\nold = SomeResource(\n    name=\"my-data\",\n    price=3.3,\n    quantity=4,\n    dangerous=False,\n    other=OtherClass(name=\"OB\"),\n    not_changed=OtherClass(name=\"Same\"),\n)\n```\n\nPassing them to `classdiff.diff` in combinations of `(None, new)`, `(old, new)`\nand `(old, None)` and printing the lines in the returned value, the following\nwill be printed with colored output (green for added, red for removed and yellow\nfor changed). Note that each element in the returned list is of type `DiffInfo`\nwhich implements `__repr__` to print with proper prefix and color.\n\n```sh\n> diff(None, new)\n----------------------------------------\n+ SomeResource(\n+   dangerous = True\n+   name = my-data\n+   not_changed = OtherClass(\n+     name = Same\n+   )\n+   other = OtherClass(\n+     name = OA\n+   )\n+   price = 2.3\n+   quantity = 4\n+ )\n\n> diff(old, new)\n----------------------------------------\n~ SomeResource(\n~   dangerous = False => True\n    name = my-data\n    not_changed = OtherClass(\n      name = Same\n    )\n~   other = OtherClass(\n~     name = OB => OA\n~   )\n~   price = 3.3 => 2.3\n    quantity = 4\n~ )\n\n> diff(old, None)\n----------------------------------------\n- SomeResource(\n-   dangerous = False\n-   name = my-data\n-   not_changed = OtherClass(\n-     name = Same\n-   )\n-   other = OtherClass(\n-     name = OB\n-   )\n-   price = 3.3\n-   quantity = 4\n- )\n\n```\n\n## Development\n\nAll code is formatted and analyzed with [`ruff`][ruff]. Tests are run with\n[`pytest`][pytest].\n\n```sh\n\u203a poetry run ruff check .\n\u203a poetry run ruff format .\n\u203a poetry run mypy .\n\u203a poetry run pytest tests/\n```\n\n[ruff]: https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/\n[pytest]: https://docs.pytest.org/en/8.2.x/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "classdiff.utils", "documentation": ["Utils for producing diff."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "classdiff.utils.IsDataclass", "bases": ["Protocol"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "classdiff.utils.IsDataclass.__dataclass_fields__", "type": {"name": "ClassVar", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.ClassVar", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["IsDataclass is the most reliable way to check for a dataclass.", "https://stackoverflow.com/a/55240861/2274551"]}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.GREEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.YELLOW", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.RED", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.ENDC", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.BOLD", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.NO_BOLD", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.UNDERLINE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.NO_UNDERLINE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.STRIKETHROUGH", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "classdiff.utils.Font.NO_STRIKETHROUGH", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Font is a class container for available colors and text formatting.\n\nIt's important to reset the value with ENDC to reset to default formatting."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "classdiff", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "classdiff.diff_object", "documentation": ["Tools that operates on objects being diffed."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "classdiff.diff_object.Format", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "classdiff.diff_object.Format.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "identifier", "type": {"name": "str | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "old_object", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "new_object", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Constructor."]}, {"name": "classdiff.diff_object.Format.prefix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project"